==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Strid
<hw>Strid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Stride</er>.]</ety> <def>A narrow passage between precipitous rocks
or banks, which looks as if it might be crossed at a stride.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Howitt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This striding place is called the <qex>Strid</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stride</ent>⟦br⟧
